KATSINA â€“The winner of the Katsina talent hunt will go home with a brand new Toyota Highlander The state commissioner of Information, Culture and Home Affairs, Alhaji Abdulkarim Yahaya Sirika disclosed this while addressing newsmen on the activities of the event in Katsina on Sunday. He added that there will also be three prizes for winners in each of the four categories. According to him the four categories include that arts and culture, automotive modeling and products, ICT design and music and entertainment. The first position for each category will get a reward of N5 million, the second position N3 million and the third position N1.5 million. In addition to this, Sirika said 100 participants will be rewarded with N100,000 each. He disclosed that governors of the North-West zone will participate in the closing ceremony of the event. The commissioner added that other dignitaries expected at the event include, the minister of science and technology, minister of communication and digital economy, minister of Aviation, minister of state FCT, minister of sports and minister of women affairs. POLL 